A. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design Low-Level Design for Snake and Ladder Game.

Requirements:

The game is played by 2 or more players on a board of size N x N (usually 10x10 = 100 cells).
Players roll a dice (1 to 6) and move their token.
If a player lands on the bottom of a Ladder, they climb up to the top.
If a player lands on the head of a Snake, they slide down to the tail.
First player to reach the exact last cell (usually 100) wins.
Support multiple players taking turns.
Handle exact landing on the final cell (no overshooting).

Constraints:

In-memory implementation.
Board size is fixed (e.g., 10x10).
Simple dice roll (random 1-6).

Edge Cases:

Landing exactly on 100.
Overshooting the last cell (should not move).
Landing on snake/ladder multiple times in one turn.
Two players on the same cell.

