Q1. How do you handle overshooting the last cell?
Answer: In getNextPosition(), if newPos > 100, we return the old position (no move).

Q2. Can two players be on the same cell?
Answer: Yes, the current design allows it. We can add a check if required.

Q3. How would you make this a GUI-based game?
Answer: Use Observer pattern so Board can notify all players when position changes.

Q4. How the winner is decided here?
In standard Snake and Ladder rules:
The game ends immediately when the first player reaches the exact winning position (usually 100).
That player is declared the Winner (1st place).
The remaining players are considered losers.
The game does NOT continue for 2nd, 3rd, or nth place.
Traditional board game rules (physical Snake & Ladder) work this way.
It keeps the game simple and focused on the "first to finish" concept.